@startuml
title Ontology Diagram Editor - Event Emission and Consumption

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #405060
  LifeLineBorderColor #9AA6B2
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #F7F9FB
  ParticipantBorderColor #536475
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ActorBorderColor #536475
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  DatabaseBorderColor #536475
  DatabaseBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  GroupBorderColor #9AA6B2
  GroupBackgroundColor #F7F9FB
  BoxBorderColor #9AA6B2
  BoxBackgroundColor #F7F9FB
}

actor User

box "Visual Studio Code Extension Host" #F7F9FB
  participant "Command\nRegistry" as Commands
  participant "Model Tree" as Tree
  participant "Event Bus" as Bus
  participant "Persistence\nService" as Persistence
  participant "Document\nController" as Document
  participant "Ontology\nLoader" as Ontology
  participant "Theme/Image\nWatchers" as Watchers
end box

box "Diagram Webview" #F7F9FB
  participant "Canvas\nSurface" as Canvas
  participant "Floating\nToolbar" as Toolbar
  participant "Property\nPanel" as Panel
  participant "Renderer" as Renderer
end box

database ".odiagram\nfile" as ODiagram
database ".otheme /\nimages" as Assets
collections "Ontology\nfiles" as OntologyFiles

legend right
  Solid arrows: command, state change, or emitted event
  Dashed arrows: event consumption / reaction
  Persistence events: document updated -> save requested -> saved/failed
endlegend

== Open Diagram and Initial Render ==

User -> Commands : Open .odiagram
Commands -> Document : open text document
Document -> ODiagram : read YAML
Document -> Bus : Canvas opened
Bus --> Tree : refresh model tree
Tree -> Ontology : load referenced ontologies
Ontology -> OntologyFiles : parse files
Ontology -> Bus : Model tree refreshed
Bus --> Renderer : render current diagram
Renderer -> Assets : load theme/images
Renderer -> Bus : Canvas rendered
Renderer -> Bus : Canvas validation changed
Bus --> Canvas : show scene, warnings, errors
Bus --> Commands : update command enablement

== Model Tree Selection and Drag/Drop ==

User -> Tree : select ontology item
Tree -> Bus : Model tree selection changed
Bus --> Canvas : select matching node/edge when unique
Canvas -> Bus : Canvas selection changed
Bus --> Tree : sync selection back to ontology item

User -> Tree : drag ontology item
Tree -> Bus : Model tree item dragged
Bus --> Canvas : provide drag payload
Canvas -> Bus : Canvas edge preview started
Canvas -> Bus : Canvas edge preview changed
User -> Canvas : drop on canvas
Canvas -> Bus : Model tree item dropped on canvas

alt Node-capable item
  Canvas -> Bus : Canvas node created
else Connection-capable item
  Canvas -> Bus : Canvas edge created
  Canvas -> Bus : Canvas node created\n(for missing endpoints)
end

Bus --> Persistence : persist valid completed gesture

== Canvas Edits and Persistence ==

User -> Canvas : move, resize, delete,\nedit text, move edge label
Canvas -> Bus : Canvas drag started / changed
Canvas -> Bus : Canvas drag completed
Canvas -> Bus : Canvas text edited
Canvas -> Bus : Canvas edge route changed
Canvas -> Bus : Canvas elements deleted
Bus --> Persistence : persist changed fields

User -> Toolbar : change style
Toolbar -> Bus : Canvas style changed
Bus --> Persistence : persist style override

User -> Panel : edit property field
Panel -> Bus : Canvas property edited
Bus --> Persistence : persist property edit

Persistence -> Document : apply one logical text edit
Document -> Bus : Diagram document updated
Persistence -> Bus : Diagram save requested
Document -> ODiagram : save file

alt Save succeeds
  Persistence -> Bus : Diagram saved
else Document update or disk save fails
  Persistence -> Bus : Diagram save failed
  Bus --> Canvas : show persistence error
  Bus --> Panel : keep displayed values\nconsistent with document state
end

Bus --> Renderer : rerender from updated document
Renderer -> Bus : Canvas rendered
Bus --> Canvas : update visible diagram
Bus --> Tree : refresh dependent selection/state

== Undo and Redo ==

User -> Commands : Undo / Redo
Commands -> Bus : Canvas undo requested\nor Canvas redo requested
Bus --> Persistence : use VS Code document undo/redo
Persistence -> Document : restore document state
Document -> Bus : Diagram document updated
Persistence -> Bus : Diagram save requested
Document -> ODiagram : save restored state
Persistence -> Bus : Diagram saved
Bus --> Renderer : rerender restored state

== Watched File Updates ==

Watchers -> Bus : theme, ontology, or image file changed
Bus --> Ontology : reload ontology metadata
Ontology -> Bus : Model tree refreshed
Bus --> Renderer : reload theme/images\nand rerender
Renderer -> Bus : Canvas rendered
Renderer -> Bus : Canvas validation changed
Bus --> Canvas : update diagram and warnings
Bus --> Tree : refresh tree state

note over Bus
Events carry the diagram file path plus the changed identifiers or payload
fields subscribers need. Components react through events rather than reading
webview DOM state or duplicating persistence logic.
end note

note over Persistence,Document
Preview updates are emitted during interaction but are not persisted.
Only completed gestures become document edits.
end note

@enduml
